Maria Riesch Beats Vonn in World Cup Super-G; Mario Matt Wins Men's Slalom

-- B y   J a m e s   C o n e
-- 
2011-02-27T13:59:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-27/maria-riesch-beats-vonn-in-world-cup-super-g-mario-matt-wins-men-s-slalom.html
Maria Riesch beat World Cup rival
Lindsey Vonn in today’s super-G to stretch her lead atop the
overall standings, while  Austria ’s Mario Matt won the men’s
slalom.  Riesch clocked 1 minute, 13.24 seconds in Are,  Sweden , to
edge the American by one-hundredth of a second. Julia Mancuso of
the U.S. was third.  The 26-year Riesch moves to 1,516 points in the overall
competition, with Vonn on 1,320. Vonn, 26, remains top in the
super-G standings with a 131-point advantage over Riesch.  Matt finished ahead of countryman Reinfried Herbst and  France ’s Jean-Baptiste Grange in Bansko,  Bulgaria , today.
Overall World Cup leader Ivica Kostelic of  Croatia , who did not
finish his first run, still tops the slalom standings.  To contact the reporter on this story:  James Cone  in  London  at 
 jcone@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editors responsible for this story:  Christopher Elser  at   celser@bloomberg.net . 